    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "\"essential tools\"... that's quite a strong way to put it. do you think there's any real validity to the argument that it's just a regressive tax that punishes people who don't have the luxury of living near a subway station? i've heard people say it's basically just a way to squeeze money out of the working class while the wealthy just pay the toll and keep driving.",
